# Blog Project Rules

## Project Overview

- Personal blog by Kota Yagi (SRE @ Money Forward)
- Built with **Hugo** and the **Blowfish** theme
- Deployed to GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions (`main` branch triggers deploy)
- Live site: https://yagikota.github.io/blog/

## Directory Structure

- `content/posts/` — Blog posts (each post is a directory with `index.md` + images)
- `config/_default/` — Hugo & theme configuration (TOML)
- `themes/blowfish/` — Theme (git submodule, do NOT edit)
- `layouts/` — Hugo layout overrides
- `assets/` — Custom CSS/JS overrides
- `static/` — Static files (images, favicon, etc.)
- `scripts/` — Utility scripts (favicon generation)
- `.github/workflows/hugo.yml` — CI/CD pipeline

## Blog Post Conventions

### Creating a New Post

1. Create a new directory under `content/posts/<post-slug>/`
2. Add an `index.md` file with the required frontmatter
3. Place images in the same directory as `index.md`
4. Add a `featured.png` for the post thumbnail

### Frontmatter Template

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title Here"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
draft: false
summary: "A concise one-sentence summary for card previews."
description: "A longer description for SEO and metadata."
tags: ["Tag1", "Tag2"]
categories: ["Category"]
series: []
showTableOfContents: true
---
```

### Writing Style

- Posts are written in **English**
- Use H2 (`##`) as the top-level heading within post content (H1 is the title)
- Table of contents is generated from H2–H4 headings
- Inline images use relative paths: `![alt text](image-name.png)`
- Add source references below images in parentheses when citing external content
- Use Markdown for all formatting; raw HTML is supported (`goldmark.renderer.unsafe = true`)

### Featured Images

- Each post should have a `featured.png` in its directory
- Use 16:9 aspect ratio
- Style: cyberpunk-themed, neon lights, dark futuristic city, no text or logos

### Existing Categories & Tags

- Categories: `Career`, `Development`
- Common tags: `SRE`, `Growth`, `Leadership`, `Productivity`, `MCP`, `Cursor`, `AI`, `DevOps`, `Observability`

## Configuration

- Hugo config files are in `config/_default/` (TOML format)
- Theme parameters: `config/_default/params.toml`
- Site settings: `config/_default/config.toml`
- Language/author: `config/_default/languages.en.toml`
- Navigation menus: `config/_default/menus.en.toml`

## Important Reminders

- **Never edit files under `themes/blowfish/`** — it is a git submodule
- The `public/` directory is the build output; it is gitignored
- Hugo version: `0.155.2` (set in `.github/workflows/hugo.yml`)
- To preview locally: `hugo server -D`
- To create a new post scaffold: `hugo new posts/<slug>/index.md`
